Rear Seat
SEATS
3. Rear Seat
A: REMOVAL
1) Disconnect the ground cable from battery and wait for at least 60 seconds before starting work. <Ref. to
NT-5, BATTERY, NOTE, Note.>
NOTE:
For models other than STI model, disconnect the ground terminal from battery sensor.
CAUTION:
Airbag system satellite safing sensor is located in the lower of the rear seat cushion center. Before
removing the rear seat, refer to CAUTION of General Description in AIRBAG SYSTEM section.
<Ref. to AB-9, CAUTION, General Description.>
The airbag system is fitted with a backup power supply. After disconnecting the battery ground ca-
ble, the airbag may operate if you do not wait for 60 seconds before starting the service of airbag sys-
tem.
2) Remove the rear seat cushion assembly.
(1) Push the corners of the rear seat cushion from above.
(2) While pushing the corners of the rear seat cushion from above, pull the knob of the hook - seat cush-
ion rear towards yourself.
(3) While pulling the knob towards yourself, disconnect the hooks by lifting up the rear seat cushion.

3) Remove the backrest assembly LH.
(1) Tilt the backrest assembly LH forward.
(2) Remove the clips located at the bottom of the cover COMPL - rear backrest LH and RH of the rear
seat back.

B: INSTALLATION
1) Install the backrest assembly RH and LH.
Tightening torque:
33 Nm (3.4 kgf-m, 24.3 ft-lb)
NOTE:
After installing the backrest assembly, make sure that each seat belt operates normally.
Make sure that they are properly secured on each hook on the vehicle side.
2) Install the rear seat cushion assembly.
3) Connect the battery ground terminal. <Ref. to NT-5, BATTERY, NOTE, Note.>
NOTE:
For models other than STI model, connect the ground terminal to battery sensor.
Tightening torque:
Refer to COMPONENT of General Description. <Ref. to SE-7, REAR SEAT, COMPONENT, Gen-
eral Description.>
C: DISASSEMBLY
1) Remove the rear seat. <Ref. to SE-29, REMOVAL, Rear Seat.>
2) Remove the headrest assembly - rear backrest.
3) Remove the knob - backrest. (Screw-in type)

14) Remove the hog rings (A), then remove the cover - rear cushion.
D: ASSEMBLY
CAUTION:
Do not reuse hog rings.
Secure the hog ring using hog ring pliers.
Install the hog rings to the specified points securely and make sure that there is no wrinkle or twist-
ing on the cover COMPL - rear backrest.
1) Assemble the cover COMPL - rear backrest and the cover - rear cushion in the same manner as for the
front seat. <Ref. to SE-23, ASSEMBLY, Front Seat.>
2) Install the hog rings (A) on the back side of the rear seat cushion assembly.
3) Install the hog rings and wire clip, then install the cover COMPL - rear backrest LH.
NOTE:
Do not contaminate or damage the cover COMPL - rear backrest and the cover - rear cushion.
While installing the hog rings, prevent the cover COMPL - rear backrest and the cover - rear cushion from
getting wrinkled.
4) Install the plastic fastener and hog ring, and then install the headrest cover.
5) Install the pad assembly - main LH.
6) Install the bushing - headrest and the bushing - lock assembly.
7) Install the lock assembly - rear backrest rear LH.
Tightening torque:
22.5 Nm (2.3 kgf-m, 16.6 ft-lb)
8) Install the plastic hooks on the back side of the backrest assembly LH.
9) Install the clips on the backside of the cover COMPL - rear backrest LH.
10) Install the knob - backrest. (Screw-in type)
11) Referring to the above steps, install the pad assembly - main RH.
Tightening torque:
Refer to COMPONENT of General Description. <Ref. to SE-7, REAR SEAT, COMPONENT, Gen-
eral Description.>
12) Install the headrest assembly - rear backrest.
13) Before installation, check the following items.
No tear and fray on the cover COMPL - rear backrest and the cover - rear cushion.
No fray or deformation on each wire cable.
14) Install the rear seat. <Ref. to SE-33, INSTALLATION, Rear Seat.>
